***<br>
He focused solely on the opponent before him, an unatural zombie animated from beyond the grave, a blight to all that was decent and good. His picks drove home time and time again ripping the undead automaton apart, bit by bit.<br>
<br>
Suddenly throughout the Estate of Unrest a great call was heard...<br>
<br>
&quot;TRAIN!&quot;<br>
<br>
Damn gnomes, always bragging about their newfangled contraptions of clockwork and steam. He would not let the shout distract him from his purpose, this blight of smelly undeadness would fall before him, looking at the gnomish machine could come later.<br>
<br>
Victory was almost his, the undead was nearly torn to bits, just a few more true strikes with his trusty picks would rid NOrrath of yet another abomination.<br>
<br>
Suddenly he was surrounded by the death screams of elves and gnomes and a human or two. Not even allowing this to distract him his only concern was the destruction of his foe.<br>
<br>
Pain lanced through him as something struck him from behind. Daring a look he let out a horrifed gasp. A small army had ammassed behind him. Hags, massive skeletons, an angry dwarven ghost, mummies, ghouls and of all things a large hand?<br>
<br>
Where the hell was that gnomish train now when he needed it? A swift moving engine would really come in handy to get him outta this one. Eyeing the dead gnomes on the ground he decided the undead horde had probaly ambushed the train and claimed it for themselves. Damn his luck.<br>
<br>
Before he could blink they were upon him. An instant later he was standing naked outside of Kaladim, saved by the grace of Brell though not understanding why Brell's penance for his aid always involved him running across the world naked as the day he was born.<br>
<br>
After running across the drafty area known as Dagnor's Cauldron (holding a branch over his parts for modesties sake) he finally made it back into Unrest....<br>
<br>
to be greeted by a ghoul, a bony bartender, 3 undead monks and a werebat to boot.<br>
<br>
the attack from the ghoul left him paralyzed, unable to move.<br>
<br>
&quot;TRAIN TO ZONE!&quot; sounded across the estate<br>
<br>
Well good fer them he thought, sounds like the gnomes had recaptured their clockwork engine and were hightailing it out of there with it before the undead hijacked them again...<br>
<br>
He then remembered his predicament and looked back to the werebat and company. Something in the werebat's eye told him he was in for more than a leg humpin.<br>
<br>
Soon the sound of Brell's voice filled his mind as the Duke of Below spoke the words to transport him bare-buttedly to safety, a curious chant it was...<br>
<br>
&quot;LOADING PLEASE WAIT&quot;<br>
<br>
****<br>
<br>
Aye, sometimes the tables are turned an' the hunter becomes that hunted.<br>
<br>
