<br>
Turning a corner, a small seahorse slammed into her, sending them both into the walls. The young thing was clearly aggitated and fearful... looking at her with pleading eyes for help. It was then that she noticed the cuts and and the coppery taste of blood in the water. The mermaid carefully picked up the injured and frightened seahorse and craddled it in her arms. She would take it the keep's healers. But how did the little thing get these cuts?<br>
<br>
Suddenly, she could sense a disturbence in the water from the direction the seahorse came.<br>
<br>
Air breathers!<br>
<br>
&quot;There's one!,&quot; shouted an invader as he clumsily tried to swim down the cooridor towards her.<br>
<br>
